    "Although quantization, model distillation, and streaming decoding architectures have been explored to reduce latency, real-time, fully multimodal LLM-based interaction remains an active research problem.Overall, while Speech LLMs demonstrate increasingly competitive robustness in both controlled evaluation settings and real-world corpora, their performance and practicality in truly diverse, noise-rich, multilingual, and low-latency scenarios remain limited.",
    "Addressing these challenges is essential for advancing Speech LLMs toward reliable, real-world conversational intelligence.TABLE VII: Comparison of multilingual ASR performance on the FLEURS dataset (average WER across 19 languages).",
    "Category Model WER ↓ E2E specialized model Whisper Large-v2 8.86 Whisper Large-v3 6.52 Open-source SLLM Qwen2.5-Omni 14.04 Qwen3-Omni-30B-A3B-Instruct 5.33 Qwen3-Omni-Flash-Instruct 5.31 Proprietary SLLM GPT-4o-Transcribe 4.48 Gemini-2.5-Pro 5.55 Languages included: Arabic, Cantonese, Chinese, Dutch, English, French, German, Indonesian, Italian, Japanese, Korean, Malay, Portuguese, Russian, Spanish, Thai, Turkish, Urdu, and Vietnamese.",
    "To further investigate the limitations observed in the performance section, we conducted a series of experiments aimed at clarifying and localizing the underlying issues.",
    "Building on the multidimensional perspective introduced in Section II-B, we identify two main categories of challenges."
